BBC Radio 4 announces a five-and-a-half-hour celebration of James Joyce's Ulysses on this coming Bloomsday, claiming it as the novel's first full-length dramatisation in Britain. (The Guardian)Strathclyde Police warns against use of the legal intoxicant Annihilation (or Mary Joy), which has previously been noted in the Shetland Isles, Lancashire and Tyneside. (BBC)